items.name: binomial-poisson-modeling
items.description: A project on categorical data analysis and discrete probability models using R. Includes café customer behavior observations, variable classification, and simulations with Binomial and Poisson distributions. Features parameter estimation, chi-square goodness-of-fit, and visualizations.

items.name: ml-lab1-salary-prediction
items.description: This repository contains Lab 01 of the Machine Learning course, focusing on predicting salaries using simple linear regression in R. It includes data exploration, correlation analysis, model building, and visualization of the relationship between years of experience and salary.

items.name: spam-detection-ml
items.description: A machine learning-based spam detection project using a synthetic dataset of email features. Implements data preprocessing, model training, and evaluation with metrics like accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score to classify emails as HAM or SPAM.

items.name: ml-preprocessing-vs-raw
items.description: This repository explores the impact of data preprocessing on regression modeling using the Carseats dataset. It compares models built with raw data versus preprocessed data, highlighting improvements through handling missing values, outliers, scaling, and encoding categorical features.

items.name: fit-and-residuals-emphasizes-model-fitting-and-diagnostics.
items.description: Exploring linear regression models in R using real (Carseats) and simulated data. This project covers predictor selection, multicollinearity, confidence intervals, and model diagnostics such as residual analysis and Cook’s distance. A hands-on dive into regression assumptions and insights.
